Lotka-Volterra model integration¶

In [1]:
import numpy as np

#parameters
c_xx = 0.1
c_xy = 0.002
c_yx = 0.0025
c_yy = 0.2

#variables
ntsteps = 1000
t = np.linspace(0,100, ntsteps)
h=t[1]-t[0]

x1 = np.zeros(ntsteps)
x1[0] = 80

y1= np.zeros(ntsteps)
y1[0] = 20

def dydt(x,y):
    return c_yx*y*x - c_yy*y

def dxdt(x,y):
    return c_xx*x - c_xy*y*x

Euler method¶

In [2]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def euler(x,y):
    for j in range(ntsteps-1):
        x[j+1] = x[j] + dxdt(x[j],y[j])*h
        y[j+1] = y[j] + dydt(x[j],y[j])*h
    return (x,y)

fig, ax = plt.subplots()
ax.plot(t,euler(x1,y1)[0])
ax.plot(t,euler(x1,y1)[1])
plt.show()

fig, ax = plt.subplots()
ax.plot(euler(x1,y1)[0],euler(x1,y1)[1])
plt.show()

Euler-Cromer method¶

In [3]:
def euler_cromer(x,y):
    for j in range(ntsteps-1):
        y[j+1] = y[j] + dydt(x[j],y[j])*h
        x[j+1] = x[j] + dxdt(x[j],y[j+1])*h      
    return (x,y)

fig, ax = plt.subplots()
ax.plot(t,euler_cromer(x1,y1)[0])
ax.plot(t,euler_cromer(x1,y1)[1])
plt.show()

fig, ax = plt.subplots()
ax.plot(euler_cromer(x1,y1)[0],euler_cromer(x1,y1)[1])
plt.show()

Verlet method¶

In [4]:
def verlet(x,y):   
    for j in range(ntsteps-1):
        y_2 = y[j] + dydt(x[j],y[j])*h*0.5 
        x[j+1] = x[j] + dxdt(x[j],y_2)*h     
        y[j+1] = y_2 + dydt(x[j+1],y_2)*h*0.5
    return (x,y)

fig, ax = plt.subplots()
ax.plot(t,verlet(x1,y1)[0])
ax.plot(t,verlet(x1,y1)[1])
plt.show()

fig, ax = plt.subplots()
ax.plot(verlet(x1,y1)[0],verlet(x1,y1)[1])
plt.show()

Runge-Kutta 4th order method¶

In [5]:
def RK_method(x,y):
    for j in range(ntsteps-1):
        k1x = dxdt(x[j],y[j])
        k1y = dydt(x[j],y[j])
        k2x = dxdt(x[j]+h*k1x/2,y[j]+h*k1y/2)
        k2y = dydt(x[j]+h*k1x/2,y[j]+h*k1y/2)
        k3x = dxdt(x[j]+h*k2x/2,y[j]+h*k2y/2)
        k3y = dydt(x[j]+h*k2x/2,y[j]+h*k2y/2)
        k4x = dxdt(x[j]+h*k3x,y[j]+h*k3y)
        k4y = dydt(x[j]+h*k3x,y[j]+h*k3y)
        x[j+1] = x[j] + 1/6*h*(k1x + 2*k2x + 2*k3x + k4x)
        y[j+1] = y[j] + 1/6*h*(k1y + 2*k2y + 2*k3y + k4y)           
    return (x,y) 

fig, ax = plt.subplots()
ax.plot(t,RK_method(x1,y1)[0])
ax.plot(t,RK_method(x1,y1)[1])
plt.show()

fig, ax = plt.subplots()
ax.plot(RK_method(x1,y1)[0],RK_method(x1,y1)[1])
plt.show()

Python scipy integration¶

In [6]:
import scipy.integrate as int
  
def derivative(X, t, c_xx, c_xy, c_yx, c_yy):
    x, y = X
    dx=dxdt(x,y)
    dy=dydt(x,y)
    return np.array([dx, dy])

pop = int.odeint(derivative, (80,20), t=t, args = (c_xx, c_xy, c_yx, c_yy))
x, y = pop.T

fig, ax = plt.subplots()
ax.plot(t,x)
ax.plot(t,y)
plt.show()

fig, ax = plt.subplots()
ax.plot(x,y)
plt.show()

def error(f):
    V = c_yx*(f(x1,y1)[0])-c_yy*np.log(f(x1,y1)[0])+c_xy*(f(x1,y1)[1])-c_xx*np.log(f(x1,y1)[1])
    return V

fig, ax = plt.subplots()
ax.set_xlabel('t')
ax.set_ylabel('V')
ax.plot(t,error(f=RK_method), label='RK')
ax.plot(t,error(f=euler), label='Euler')
ax.plot(t,error(f=euler_cromer), label= 'Euler-Cromer')
ax.plot(t,error(f=verlet), label='Verlet')
ax.plot(t,c_yx*x-c_yy*np.log(x)+c_xy*y-c_xx*np.log(y), label='scipy')
ax.legend()
plt.show()
